    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create legislation to prevent COVID-19 & vaccine misinformation on social media",
        "additional_details": "A survey of 8,000 people in the US & UK by the Vaccine Confidence Project found people's willingness to take a Covid vaccine dropped by 6.4% after reading anti-vax posts.\r\n\r\nMisinformation on COVID-19 affects how seriously people take the pandemic. Experts are warning anti-vax posts may undermine and discourage the COVID-19 vaccine, threatening and preventing herd immunity. The vaccine is crucial to helping end the pandemic. However, the spread of misinformation may prevent it from working.",
        "background": "Government needs to create legislation that:\r\n\r\n-Fines tech giants failing to remove COVID & vaccine misinformation\r\n-Stops anti-vax posts being promoted",
